                <note rend="inline" type="source">367n.1113Ganani, Samuel/6: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Jerusalem</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Knabenshue</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-09-14T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 14, 1929—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your August 25, 8 P.M. reported twelve American citizens killed at Hebron. Eight
                    of these are listed in your August 26, 10 P.M. and your telegram of September
                        11th<note n="45" xml:id="d39fn45">Not printed.</note> reported Samuel
                    Genandi [<hi rend="italic">Ganani?</hi>] as having died from wounds. Urgently
                    telegraph names of any American citizens killed other than those listed in two
                    telegrams mentioned above.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
